This paper discusses the classic relational algebra operators and their properties, which are fundamental concepts in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses lattice axioms and their application to the set of operators, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper's focus on reducing the set of operators to two binary operations may suggest that it belongs to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these sub-categories often deal with optimization and simplification of algorithms.
